SIMPLE: mainor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mainor
<hw>Main"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Anglo-Norm.
<ets>meinoure</ets>, OF. <ets>manuevre</ets>. See
<er>Maneuver</er>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A thing stolen
found on the person of the thief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A thief was said to be ⟦ldquo⟧taken with the
<xex>mainor</xex>,⟦rdquo⟧ when he was taken with the thing stolen upon
him, that is, <xex>in his hands</xex>.</note> <rj><au>Wharton.</au>
<au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mainpernable</ent>⟦br⟧
